  <span id="freeText235860289410511705" style="display:none">Ok, so this is MY opinion on The Slave, so pardon me if you did not like it. I was waiting impatiently to finish this book, I honestly don't know why exactly, but because I have a rule of thumb to finish the book whether it's good or bad if I pass 30 pages, I had to complete the novel. The plot is good, and, in fact, one that is new to me. However, Singer talked so much about Judaism to the point that I didn't understand a couple of pages because he included so many Jewish terms without even explaining them. He really shows the love Wanda had for Jacob in a very nice way. I mean, Wanda literally sacrificed so much to marry him (I honestly don't know why). He also loved her so much that he committed several sins for her sake (he was a very very very religious Jewish guy). <br />Anyways, the book was ok.</span>
